  "prompt": "How do I know if someone blocks me on Facebook messenger?",
  "response": "If you suspect that someone has blocked you on Facebook Messenger, there are a few signs to look for:\n\n1. **Message Delivery Status**: When you send a message, if it shows as \"Sent\" but never changes to \"Delivered\" or \"Read,\" it could indicate that you've been blocked.\n\n2. **Profile Picture**: If the person's profile picture has vanished or is replaced with a generic silhouette, they may have blocked you.\n\n3. **Conversation History**: You may still see the conversation in your Messenger app, but if you can't send messages or your messages don't get through, this is a red flag.\n\n4. **Search Functionality**: If you try to search for the person in Messenger, and you cannot find them, it may be another indication of being blocked.\n\n5. **Viewing Their Profile**: If you try to view their profile on Facebook and can't access it, they might have either blocked you or deactivated their account.\n\nRemember that these signs are not definitive proof, as the person might have privacy settings adjusted, changed their profile, or deactivated their account. The only sure way to know would be to communicate with them directly through another means.",
